A RESOLUTION
1 Designating the month of April as Community Activist Month; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Community Activist Month recognizes individuals with spirit, vision, values,
3 leadership, and transformational activism who create a better tomorrow for generations yet
4 to be born; and
5 WHEREAS, Community Activist Month will focus on "activism" and "activist," which are
6 terms that date back to the slave revolts of the first century BC in the Roman Empire as well
7 as the civil actions and new social movements of the 1960s in the United States; and
8 WHEREAS, activists fight the status quo and challenge injustice to balance the scales of
9 justice and have a long history of changing the world through reform; and
10 WHEREAS, activists gather people together and build coalitions to tap into the power of
11 collaboration and collective strength and demand righteousness and change; collective action
12 that is purposeful, organized, and sustained over a period of time becomes known as a social
13 movement; and
